To using this script first install imagemagic package.

I am using Ubuntu 10.10, do following to install this package:-

apt-get install imagemagic ( run this command in sudo mode )


To resize you photos do as :-

1. Copy size.sh in your photo folder
2. run ./size.sh 

Your resize photo will move to resized-<yyyy-mm-dd> folder


NOTE: This script will compress your image and will decrease quality little bit.
      Objactive of this script is to resize photos for uploading to web
